title: Despite faceplant, Ethiopia's Yalemzerf Yehualaw becomes youngest ever London Marathon winner
description: With six miles left, Yalemzerf Yehualaw's race seemed to have been ruined after the Ethiopian was left sprawled on the road after stumbling over a speed bump.

title: 'Interview with the Vampire' has an undying legacy. Look inside its TV rebirth
description: It's been nearly half a century since "Interview with the Vampire" was published, leaving its mark on popular culture. Penned by the late Anne Rice, the book became the first of the "Vampire Chronicles," which include 12 follow-up novels. "Interview" itself was adapted into a 1994 feature film starring Brad Pitt and Tom Cruise, while a loose "Queen of the Damned" adaptation hit theaters in 2002.

title: UK PM Liz Truss admits mistakes on controversial tax cuts plan, but doubles down on it anyway
description: British Prime Minister Liz Truss admitted mistakes had been made with her government's controversial "mini-budget" announced last week -- which sent the pound to historic lows and sparked market chaos -- but stood by her policies.

title: Football Australia 'strongly condemns' fans' 'anti-social behaviour'
description: Football Australia said it will go through all the video footage and images at its disposal from Saturday night's Australia Cup final in Sydney after it was widely reported that some fans made "the Hitler Salute."

title: Brazilians vote in contentious election plagued by violence and fear
description: Polls opened in Brazil on Sunday in a presidential election marred by an unprecedented climate of tension and violence.

title: Baseball great Alex Rodriguez reflects on steroid abuse, his past with J-Lo
description: Baseball great Alex Rodriguez is opening up about mistakes in his personal and professional life, and how they are shaping his growing business empire.

title: Instruction about race may be under siege across the US, but this course is empowering students at a Southern high school
description: In the early 2000s, when I was a student at Ridge View High School, in Columbia, South Carolina, I loved to parse the legacies of certain historical figures: W.E.B. Du Bois, in AP US History; Malcolm X, in AP English Language and Composition.

title: Chinese hacking group targeting US agencies and companies has surged its activity, analysis finds
description: An elite Chinese hacking group with ties to operatives indicted by a US grand jury in 2020 has surged its activity this year, targeting sensitive data held by companies and government agencies in the US and dozens of other countries, according to an expert at consulting giant PricewaterhouseCoopers.

title: Amazon is always watching
description: A TV that knows when you're in and out of the room. A gadget that monitors your breathing pattern while you sleep. An enhanced voice assistant tool that highlights just how much it knows about your everyday life.

title: Hurricane Ian: Death toll rises to 66 in Florida
description: Days after Hurricane Ian slammed into Florida, shell-shocked residents are still assessing the damage left behind by record-high storm surge, damaging winds and catastrophic flooding that left some areas of the Sunshine State unrecognizable.

title: How Buffalo is ensuring the Black community isn't left behind after mass supermarket shooting
description: The day after Buffalo experienced the largest mass shooting in its history, teams of emergency volunteers and mental health counselors arrived on the scene, offering emotional support and distributing food.

title: London is stage for NFL's milestone 100th international game
description: The NFL returns to London on Sunday as the Minnesota Vikings (2-1) and New Orleans Saints (1-2) contest the first of five international slate of games scheduled this season.

title: Hurricane Orlene strengthens into Category 3 storm as it heads toward western Mexico
description: Rapidly intensifying Category 3 Hurricane Orlene is approaching western Mexico, where it's expected to cause life-threatening flooding, according to the National Hurricane Center.

title: 'Saturday Night Live' gets a Manningcast for its season premiere episode
description: "Saturday Night Live" kicked off its 48th season on Saturday night with host Miles Teller as former NFL quarterback Peyton Manning and Andrew Dismukes as his brother, Eli.

title: Analysis: Putin has his back to the wall with the clock ticking ever louder
description: Time is running out for Russian President Vladmir Putin, and he knows it.

title: Colorado's state fish swims back from brink of extinction
description: The greenback cutthroat trout, Colorado's state fish, was declared extinct over 50 years ago. But last week officials found the first confirmation that the trout are once again reproducing in the wild.

title: Indonesia stadium tragedy: At least 129 people reported dead following soccer match, police say
description: At least 127 people are dead and hundreds more injured, police say, after chaos and violence erupted late on Saturday following an Indonesian league soccer match between two of the nation's biggest teams.

title: Trump defends 'great woman' Ginni Thomas after Jan. 6 testimony
description: Former President Donald Trump praised the "courage and strength" of Ginni Thomas at a rally Saturday, days after the wife of Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas met with congressional investigators about her efforts to overturn the results of the 2020 election.
